contentrichtext.text: {{Infobox protected area of Australia | name = Crater Lakes National Park | iucn_category = II | image = | caption = | locator_x = | locator_y = | nearest_town_or_city = | coordinates = {{Coord|17|14|45|S|145|37|44|E|type:landmark_region:AU-QLD|display=inline,title}} | area = {{Convert|9.59|km2|sqmi|2|abbr=on}} | established = 1994 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | managing_authorities = [[Queensland Parks and Wildlife Service]] | official_site = }} '''Crater Lakes''' is a national park in [[Queensland]], [[Australia]], 1367 km northwest of [[Brisbane]]. The park contains two volcanically-formed lakes, [[Lake Barrine]] and [[Lake Eacham|Lake Eacham (Yidyam)]]. Both lakes have walking trails around the lake; boat tours are also given at Lake Barrine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nprsr.qld.gov.au/parks/crater-lakes/index.html|title=Crater Lakes National Park|author=Department of National Parks, Recreation, Sport and Racing|date=17 October 2012|publisher=Queensland Government|accessdate=15 December 2012}}</ref> ==References== {{reflist}} ==See also== {{Portal|Queensland}} * [[Protected areas of Queensland]] {{National Parks of Queensland}} [[Category:National parks of Far North Queensland]] [[Category:Protected areas established in 1994]] {{Queensland-national-park-stub}}
